00:24:05.528 --> 00:24:07.571
- like some kind of amputee fuck doll?
- No.

516
00:24:07.572 --> 00:24:09.865
- And filmed her for kicks?
- No. No. No!

517
00:24:09.866 --> 00:24:12.159
It wasn't like that. I did...

518
00:24:12.160 --> 00:24:14.786
I did everything I could
to-to keep her alive.

519
00:24:14.787 --> 00:24:17.456
to-to make her happy...

520
00:24:20.501 --> 00:24:22.210
Just listen to me.

521
00:24:22.211 --> 00:24:25.590
Okay. it wasn't all like... that.

522
00:24:29.802 --> 00:24:31.179
I couldn't let her go.

523
00:24:32.638 --> 00:24:33.931
I didn't know how.

524
00:24:36.642 --> 00:24:38.186
Because I loved her.

525
00:24:40.479 --> 00:24:41.772
And so did you.

526
00:24:44.650 --> 00:24:46.484
You're goddamn right I loved her.

527
00:24:46.485 --> 00:24:48.862
She wouldn't want us fighting over her...

528
00:24:48.863 --> 00:24:50.322
Don't fucking tell me what she would want.

529
00:24:50.323 --> 00:24:54.326
You knew her for five minutes.
I was with her for decades.

530
00:24:54.327 --> 00:24:56.244
Hold-hold-hold on.

531
00:24:56.245 --> 00:24:58.079
This-this is a setup.

532
00:24:58.080 --> 00:25:00.749
Someone's trying to separate us.

533
00:25:00.750 --> 00:25:02.584
This has been plan...

534
00:25:02.585 --> 00:25:05.212
Fucking Sage.

535
00:25:05.213 --> 00:25:06.297
It's Sage.

536
00:25:07.256 --> 00:25:08.798
You see?

537
00:25:08.799 --> 00:25:10.383
She's trying to screw with us.

538
00:25:10.384 --> 00:25:13.763
Oh. come on.
I can't find the V1 without you.

539
00:25:22.772 --> 00:25:23.773
Good.

540
00:25:26.901 --> 00:25:28.653
You don't deserve to live forever.

541
00:25:43.834 --> 00:25:46.212
Security cameras are looped.

542
00:25:56.222 --> 00:25:57.390
Who are they?

543
00:25:58.474 --> 00:26:00.058
It's almost every psychic in the country.

544
00:26:00.059 --> 00:26:03.062
What the fuck does Homelander
want with all of them?

545
00:26:24.792 --> 00:26:26.459
Oh. my God.

546
00:26:26.460 --> 00:26:28.087
It's Firecracker.

547
00:26:32.800 --> 00:26:34.301
Jesus.

548
00:26:34.302 --> 00:26:37.972
I mean. it had to be Homelander. right?

549
00:26:39.348 --> 00:26:44.019
You'd think I'd feel relieved.
but I just feel sad.

550
00:26:44.020 --> 00:26:46.188
I mean. she's a human being.

551
00:26:47.481 --> 00:26:49.650
Maybe that's why Homelander killed her.

552
00:26:53.654 --> 00:26:55.155
That a fuckin' fax machine?

553
00:26:55.156 --> 00:26:57.283
Yeah. it's the last of the numbers
she had for him.

554
00:26:58.367 --> 00:27:02.704
Oi. 23 fucking numbers you had for
Bombsight. and they're all fucking shite?

555
00:27:02.705 --> 00:27:04.749
Do you know how to delete them?

556
00:27:06.500 --> 00:27:08.376
I was telling you the truth.

557
00:27:08.377 --> 00:27:11.087
I have no idea where Bombsight is.
or how to reach him.

558
00:27:11.088 --> 00:27:12.464
So just let me go.

559
00:27:12.465 --> 00:27:15.301
Kimiko. keep an eye on her.

560
00:27:21.766 --> 00:27:23.266
Fuck do we do now?

561
00:27:23.267 --> 00:27:25.977
Fetch us some pliers
and put the screws to her.

562
00:27:25.978 --> 00:27:28.522
She knows more than she's lettin' on.

563
00:27:29.774 --> 00:27:31.274
Or she doesn't.

564
00:27:31.275 --> 00:27:34.361
I'm sorry.
but she's not that good of an actress.

565
00:27:34.362 --> 00:27:35.445
He's right.

566
00:27:35.446 --> 00:27:41.034
Ooh. I know. the villain
switching sides in the final hour?

567
00:27:41.035 --> 00:27:43.411
What a twist. a shock that never happens.

568
00:27:43.412 --> 00:27:46.706
But unclench those assholes. fellas.
I'm here to help.

569
00:27:46.707 --> 00:27:48.583
I'm a free agent now.
I came alone.

570
00:27:48.584 --> 00:27:50.919
You can shoot me in the heart
whenever you like.

571
00:27:50.920 --> 00:27:52.379
That's a good idea.

572
00:27:52.380 --> 00:27:56.341
That would go against our mutual interest.

573
00:27:56.342 --> 00:27:57.634
Which is?

574
00:27:57.635 --> 00:28:01.680
Stopping a petulant. laser-eyed narcissist
from also becoming immortal.

575
00:28:03.307 --> 00:28:05.975
I want him dead as much as you do.

576
00:28:05.976 --> 00:28:07.894
You spent the last couple of years
building Homelander up.

577
00:28:07.895 --> 00:28:09.646
And now you want to tear him down?

578
00:28:09.647 --> 00:28:11.189
Why the fuck should we trust you?

579
00:28:11.190 --> 00:28:13.650
You can't trust me.
Honestly. you shouldn't.

580
00:28:13.651 --> 00:28:15.026
But you will.

581
00:28:15.027 --> 00:28:16.528
And why would we do that?

582
00:28:16.529 --> 00:28:20.615
I know Campbell and Starlight
are headed to plant your little virus.

583
00:28:20.616 --> 00:28:23.618
You can trace anyone.
if you know what to look for.

584
00:28:23.619 --> 00:28:27.038
And you baboons. you leave a trail
of banana peels wherever you go.

585
00:28:27.039 --> 00:28:31.209
I could have stopped you.
I could have killed you. but I didn't.

586
00:28:31.210 --> 00:28:36.297
That virus is gonna
wipe out the fuckin' lot of you.

587
00:28:36.298 --> 00:28:40.635
And you don't strike me
as the suicide type.

588
00:28:40.636 --> 00:28:43.596
I will be in my nice. quiet bunker.
reading Wittgenstein in peace.

589
00:28:43.597 --> 00:28:47.976
That is. unless that bleached blonde baby

590
00:28:47.977 --> 00:28:51.354
gets his hands on V1 and survives.

591
00:28:51.355 --> 00:28:54.107
You must have realized by now
granny out there

592
00:28:54.108 --> 00:28:56.276
has no clue how to contact Bombsight.

593
00:28:56.277 --> 00:28:58.320
But I do.

594
00:28:58.988 --> 00:29:00.697
And I can get him here.

595
00:29:00.698 --> 00:29:03.242
So. let me help.

596
00:29:08.247 --> 00:29:11.833
Earlier today. there was a catastrophic
failure of a Vought Petroleum pipeline

597
00:29:11.834 --> 00:29:15.462
resulting in a significant amount
of crude oil spilling into the Bering Sea.

598
00:29:17.047 --> 00:29:19.591
Sorry. I'm just shaking off a migraine.

599
00:29:19.592 --> 00:29:21.342
But your mind is still an open book. Chad.

600
00:29:21.343 --> 00:29:23.803
Yes. the spill was larger
than <i>Deepwater Horizon.</i>

601
00:29:23.804 --> 00:29:25.096
Much larger.

602
00:29:25.097 --> 00:29:27.932
No. Jimmy. we don't know
when the rupture will be sealed.

603
00:29:27.933 --> 00:29:29.017
I'm hearing weeks. at least.

604
00:29:29.018 --> 00:29:31.769
And yes. this pipeline was Deep's baby.

605
00:29:31.770 --> 00:29:34.439
Rest assured. he's got the situation
completely under control.

606
00:29:34.440 --> 00:29:37.275
I can't breathe!
I can't breathe!

607
00:29:44.074 --> 00:29:46.242
Jeremy? No!

608
00:29:46.243 --> 00:29:49.078
No. no. no!

609
00:29:49.079 --> 00:29:51.623
No. Jeremy.

610
00:29:51.624 --> 00:29:55.001
No. no. No. no. no. no.
He's not breathing. No.

611
00:29:58.380 --> 00:29:59.923
Jeremy.

612
00:30:01.091 --> 00:30:03.301
Jeremy? Can you hear me?

613
00:30:03.302 --> 00:30:06.012
We know. Kevin.

614
00:30:06.013 --> 00:30:07.639
We know it was you.

615
00:30:26.283 --> 00:30:29.369
Why are you so certain
Bombsight will come here?

616
00:30:29.370 --> 00:30:31.996
If I sent you a picture of Kimiko tied up.

617
00:30:31.997 --> 00:30:35.917
you'd hop here as fast as
your froggy little legs could take you.

618
00:30:35.918 --> 00:30:37.752
Park Geisha over there.

619
00:30:37.753 --> 00:30:39.797
and keep an eye on her.

620
00:31:00.442 --> 00:31:04.154
I wanted to say...
I'm very sorry about this.

621
00:31:07.408 --> 00:31:10.368
I watched every episode of
<i>Undercover Geisha</i> when I was a kid.

622
00:31:10.369 --> 00:31:14.790
I loved it. even the parts that
were ridiculous. racist stereotypes.

623
00:31:16.458 --> 00:31:19.753
It meant so much to see
someone who looked like me on TV.

624
00:31:23.048 --> 00:31:26.009
We watched with Japanese subtitles.
It's how I learned English.

625
00:31:26.010 --> 00:31:29.053
If you're such a big fan. let me go.

626
00:31:29.054 --> 00:31:31.556
<i>DÃ©solÃ©.</i> but we cannot.

627
00:31:31.557 --> 00:31:34.267
Not until we get the V1
that Bombsight possesses.

628
00:31:34.268 --> 00:31:37.061
Wait. that's what you're after?

629
00:31:37.062 --> 00:31:38.396
V1?

630
00:31:41.358 --> 00:31:43.818
What-What's so funny?

631
00:31:43.819 --> 00:31:46.654
I'll tell Bombsight
to just give it to you.

632
00:31:46.655 --> 00:31:48.657
I sure as hell don't want it.

633
00:31:51.785 --> 00:31:54.579
He stole the V1 for you.

634
00:31:54.580 --> 00:31:56.832
so you two could be together forever.

635
00:32:01.920 --> 00:32:03.547
But you didn't take it.

636
00:32:05.007 --> 00:32:06.216
I said no.

637
00:32:07.509 --> 00:32:08.886
Which is why he left.

638
00:32:09.970 --> 00:32:14.850
I guess. for him.
watching me get old was too painful.

639
00:32:17.227 --> 00:32:20.689
I'm sorry. I do not understand.
Why won't you take it?

640
00:32:22.149 --> 00:32:23.609
To live forever?

641
00:32:25.277 --> 00:32:26.737
It'd be torture.

642
00:32:30.157 --> 00:32:32.743
You're both so young.
You wouldn't understand.

643
00:32:33.827 --> 00:32:35.037
Maybe I would.

644
00:32:40.668 --> 00:32:43.795
Summer is only beautiful

645
00:32:43.796 --> 00:32:46.048
when you know winter is coming.

646
00:32:59.061 --> 00:33:01.105
Is this how you feel?

647
00:33:07.319 --> 00:33:09.238
Annie and I talked about it.

648
00:33:10.614 --> 00:33:12.199
We'd have to...

649
00:33:18.414 --> 00:33:25.796
We'd have to watch you
and Hughie waste away.

650
00:33:27.631 --> 00:33:31.676
Neither of us wants to die. but...

651
00:33:31.677 --> 00:33:34.011
we don't want to be vampires. either.

652
00:33:38.016 --> 00:33:41.686
I'm sorry. I hadn't. um...

653
00:33:41.687 --> 00:33:43.312
It's okay.

654
00:33:43.313 --> 00:33:45.816
We're both willing to do it anyway.

655
00:33:47.651 --> 00:33:49.570
For you.

656
00:34:06.253 --> 00:34:07.587
Jesus Christ.

657
00:34:07.588 --> 00:34:10.215
Yeah. that's pretty much
what he was going for.

658
00:34:14.011 --> 00:34:16.012
Do I even need to say be careful?

659
00:34:16.013 --> 00:34:17.221
It's okay.

660
00:34:17.222 --> 00:34:19.724
It won't go off until the timer does.

661
00:34:19.725 --> 00:34:20.976
I think.

662
00:34:40.037 --> 00:34:42.622
Starlight...

663
00:34:44.041 --> 00:34:46.959
I was wondering who befouled
the security cameras.

664
00:34:46.960 --> 00:34:48.211
Hi. Aaron.

665
00:34:48.212 --> 00:34:49.837
It's been a while.

666
00:34:49.838 --> 00:34:54.675
The Lord is working in
His most mysterious ways this evening.

667
00:34:54.676 --> 00:34:57.512
I didn't think I would ever see you
in a house of worship again.

668
00:34:57.513 --> 00:35:01.140
Yeah. well. I didn't think I would ever
see you meat-riding Homelander so hard.

669
00:35:01.141 --> 00:35:04.477
but... I guess we're both
just full of surprises. aren't we?

670
00:35:04.478 --> 00:35:07.814
- I take it you're not here to repent.
- No.

671
00:35:07.815 --> 00:35:10.526
I'm here to... to talk sense
into an old friend.

672
00:35:11.276 --> 00:35:12.819
You did that for me. do you remember?

673
00:35:12.820 --> 00:35:14.278
When. um...

674
00:35:14.279 --> 00:35:17.490
Alex and I were gonna get those matching
tattoos and you talked us out of it.

675
00:35:17.491 --> 00:35:19.784
A tramp stamp crucifix
is a bit of a mixed message.

676
00:35:19.785 --> 00:35:22.537
Especially on a shit-faced 15-year-old.

677
00:35:22.538 --> 00:35:26.666
But if memory serves.
you weren't so grateful at the time.

678
00:35:26.667 --> 00:35:29.043
Yeah. you know. it's hard to hear
that you're making a mistake

679
00:35:29.044 --> 00:35:31.505
you could regret for
the rest of your life.

680
00:35:33.131 --> 00:35:37.134
But... I...

681
00:35:37.135 --> 00:35:40.680
God. I wanted your approval
so badly back then.

682
00:35:40.681 --> 00:35:44.767
You know. you were like
a cool older brother that I never had.

683
00:35:44.768 --> 00:35:48.063
And you weren't cynical. like Ezekiel.

684
00:35:49.606 --> 00:35:53.402
You... you believed.

685
00:35:55.028 --> 00:35:56.529
I still do.

686
00:35:56.530 --> 00:35:58.240
In Homelander?

687
00:35:59.533 --> 00:36:00.784
Come on. Aaron.

688
00:36:01.869 --> 00:36:04.412
You know. I started preaching
when I was nine years old.

689
00:36:04.413 --> 00:36:06.915
in that moldy tent in Greenwood.

690
00:36:08.292 --> 00:36:09.917
And people would come and...

691
00:36:09.918 --> 00:36:13.045
beg me to pray for them.

692
00:36:13.046 --> 00:36:15.214
heal their illness.

693
00:36:15.215 --> 00:36:17.592
look after their children.

694
00:36:17.593 --> 00:36:19.219
get them a job.

695
00:36:19.887 --> 00:36:23.640
And I raised my hands in prayer
for each of them.

696
00:36:24.558 --> 00:36:26.393
Those prayers went unanswered.

697
00:36:28.520 --> 00:36:30.646
Nobody was listening.

698
00:36:30.647 --> 00:36:32.607
God checked out.

699
00:36:32.608 --> 00:36:35.651
Homelander is standing in front of us.

700
00:36:35.652 --> 00:36:37.695
He's not asking for blind faith.

701
00:36:37.696 --> 00:36:40.823
And when I talk...
when I talk. he listens.

702
00:36:40.824 --> 00:36:43.034
God is supposed to be selfless.

703
00:36:43.035 --> 00:36:45.244
Okay? Homelander...

704
00:36:45.245 --> 00:36:47.955
Homelander doesn't care about anyone
or anything outside of himself.

705
00:36:47.956 --> 00:36:52.168
Maybe imperfect. but he...
he brought this church up out of ruin.

706
00:36:52.169 --> 00:36:55.171
He fights back against the secular forces
corrupting this nation.

707
00:36:55.172 --> 00:36:57.423
He killed Firecracker.
and you're delusional if you think

708
00:36:57.424 --> 00:36:58.841
he won't turn on you.

709
00:36:58.842 --> 00:37:02.053
Firecracker was a nonbeliever.
she brought his wrath upon herself.

710
00:37:02.054 --> 00:37:06.308
I am not afraid to stand
before Homelander's judgment!

711
00:37:12.856 --> 00:37:15.692
But you didn't sneak in here
to argue about dogma. did you?

712
00:37:18.111 --> 00:37:20.238
Oh. Annie. I am sorry.

713
00:37:22.449 --> 00:37:24.076
I really did like you.

714
00:37:47.849 --> 00:37:49.351
Stop.

715
00:37:51.144 --> 00:37:53.021
You know what this is?

716
00:37:53.647 --> 00:37:56.608
I open it. you're dead in 30 seconds.

717
00:38:01.363 --> 00:38:02.613
So is Annie.

718
00:38:02.614 --> 00:38:04.658
No.

719
00:38:06.118 --> 00:38:07.911
She already took the antidote.

720
00:38:10.205 --> 00:38:12.915
You didn't go to all this trouble
just to waste that on me.

721
00:38:12.916 --> 00:38:15.084
No...

722
00:38:15.085 --> 00:38:16.586
but I will.

723
00:38:19.464 --> 00:38:21.133
Unless you let her go.

724
00:38:30.809 --> 00:38:32.393
Don't be a stranger. Annie.

725
00:38:32.394 --> 00:38:34.438
Room for everyone in our flock.

726
00:38:41.778 --> 00:38:44.488
<i>Authorities are calling it
the worst environmental disaster</i>

727
00:38:44.489 --> 00:38:45.906
<i>in U.S. history.</i>

728
00:38:45.907 --> 00:38:50.119
<i>An estimated 2.5 million gallons
of crude oil have already spilled...</i>

729
00:38:50.120 --> 00:38:51.787
Plenty of fish in the sea. bro.

730
00:38:53.999 --> 00:38:56.542
But most of them are fuckin' dead.

731
00:38:56.543 --> 00:38:59.295
<i>...Vought Petroleum promised
a thorough investigation...</i>

732
00:38:59.296 --> 00:39:01.756
You think a fish holocaust is funny. bro?

733
00:39:01.757 --> 00:39:05.051
Uh. yeah. Payback's a bitch. bitch.

734
00:39:05.052 --> 00:39:07.595
What's that supposed to mean?

735
00:39:07.596 --> 00:39:11.265
It means I flew up to Alaska.
swam down to your dumb pipeline

736
00:39:11.266 --> 00:39:13.018
and punched a hole in it.

737
00:39:13.727 --> 00:39:15.269
It wasn't even that hard.

738
00:39:15.270 --> 00:39:17.146
That shit is really poorly built.

739
00:39:17.147 --> 00:39:20.608
What? Why?

740
00:39:20.609 --> 00:39:24.445
You killed Adam Bourke. so I killed
a bunch of porpoises or whatever.

741
00:39:24.446 --> 00:39:26.531
Now we're even steven.

742
00:39:31.119 --> 00:39:33.287
I killed one f... I killed one dude!

743
00:39:33.288 --> 00:39:35.664
You killed 1.4 billion fish. motherfucker!

744
00:39:35.665 --> 00:39:39.418
One human being who was
a national treasure. asshole.

745
00:39:39.419 --> 00:39:41.587
Not just some stupid fish.

746
00:39:44.424 --> 00:39:46.301
They were my friends.

747
00:39:48.512 --> 00:39:50.763
Sucks to suck. dipshit.

748
00:39:50.764 --> 00:39:53.558
<i>Stop. loser. bro-bro-bro!</i>

749
00:39:54.559 --> 00:39:57.103
So let's record
this stupid fucking thing.

750
00:40:21.169 --> 00:40:23.754
You were never my bro. bro.

751
00:40:40.021 --> 00:40:41.523
No.

752
00:40:49.489 --> 00:40:50.991
Oh. God.

753
00:40:58.248 --> 00:40:59.541
Oh. God.

754
00:41:08.300 --> 00:41:11.969
Hey. Some kid shit on the floor
in the men's room. Again.

755
00:41:11.970 --> 00:41:14.472
Terrific.

756
00:41:26.985 --> 00:41:32.615
Bubelah. You might not remember.
but we actually met. back-back in the day.

757
00:41:32.616 --> 00:41:34.658
You must have been yay-high.
but you know what?

758
00:41:34.659 --> 00:41:37.912
I-I saw greatness in you. even then.

759
00:41:37.913 --> 00:41:39.705
I don't remember that. Chet.

760
00:41:39.706 --> 00:41:42.583
I did.

761
00:41:42.584 --> 00:41:44.919
- Um...
- Well.

762
00:41:44.920 --> 00:41:47.171
we needed to talk in private.

763
00:41:47.172 --> 00:41:48.881
Okay.

764
00:41:48.882 --> 00:41:54.053
I take it you saw the security footage
from the old folks' home.

765
00:41:54.054 --> 00:41:56.931
And you probably got
the very reasonable impression

766
00:41:56.932 --> 00:42:00.517
that I'm somehow working
